                            <comment id="17938638" author="janhoy" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2025 15:19:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi. Please provide more details on your environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Windows version&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Using CMD or Powershell or something else?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;How was solr installed?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;What user are you when running Solr?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;What happens if you type &quot;wmic&quot; in the terminal&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;What happens if you type&#160;&quot;C:\Windows\System32\wbem\wmic.exe&quot; in terminal?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;What is your PATH?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17938809" author="JIRAUSER309108" created="Thu, 27 Mar 2025 06:14:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Windows version&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Edition &#160; &#160;Windows 11 Home&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Version &#160; &#160;24H2&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
*Installed on &#160; &#160;&#8206;18-&#8206;02-&#8206;2025*&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;OS build &#160; &#160;26100.3476&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Experience &#160; &#160;Windows Feature Experience Pack 1000.26100.54.0&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using CMD or Powershell or something else?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;using cmd&lt;/b&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How was solr installed?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;checked out from solr dev branch&lt;/b&gt;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
What user are you when running Solr?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;Administrator&lt;/b&gt;&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
What happens if you type &quot;wmic&quot; in the terminal&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;C:\solr\solr\packaging\build\dev\bin&amp;gt;wmic&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&apos;wmic&apos; is not recognized as an internal or external command,&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;operable program or batch file.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
What happens if you type &quot;C:\Windows\System32\wbem\wmic.exe&quot; in terminal?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;C:\&amp;gt;C:\Windows\System32\wbem\wmic.exe&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&apos;C:\Windows\System32\wbem\wmic.exe&apos; is not recognized as an internal or external command,&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;operable program or batch file&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
What is your PATH?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;b&gt;PATH=C:\windows\system32;C:\windows;C:\windows\System32\Wbem;C:\windows\System32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0\;C:\windows\System32\OpenSSH\;C:\Program Files\Git\cmd;C:\Users\gaurt\AppData\Local\Microsoft\WindowsApps;C:\Users\gaurt\AppData\Local\GitHubDesktop\bin&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17938819" author="JIRAUSER309108" created="Thu, 27 Mar 2025 07:00:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;On installing wmic solr starts successfully.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17938856" author="janhoy" created="Thu, 27 Mar 2025 09:21:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like MS is about to remove the tool altogether &lt;a href=&quot;https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/windows-itpro-blog/how-to-install-wmic-feature-on-demand-on-windows-11/4189530&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/windows-itpro-blog/how-to-install-wmic-feature-on-demand-on-windows-11/4189530&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17938887" author="janhoy" created="Thu, 27 Mar 2025 10:45:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, the reason for this code being triggered is that in &lt;tt&gt;solr.cmd&lt;/tt&gt; we actually use the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/solr/blob/main/solr/bin/solr.cmd#L1172&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;updated status tool&lt;/a&gt; to check if solr has started, which in turn calls wmic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m going to attempt a fix where we call out to &lt;tt&gt;powershell.exe&lt;/tt&gt; instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17945517" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 17 Apr 2025 21:28:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 6315d3fe2ca46fe7a30a33f4b8deea906d7090c0 in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/main from Jan H&#248;ydahl&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=6315d3fe2ca&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=6315d3fe2ca&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17717&quot; title=&quot;On starting solr in windows wmic file not found&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-17717&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-17717&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Use Powershell instead of WMIC to get cmdline on Windows (#3291)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17945518" author="janhoy" created="Thu, 17 Apr 2025 21:35:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gmt425&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gmt425&quot;&gt;gmt425&lt;/a&gt; I merged a fix to main branch. If you want to verify the fix before we release solr 9.9, please check out solr&apos;s main branch, build a custom snapshot build and give it a spin. If you don&apos;t fancy building solr yourself, wait about 12 hours for the next nighly build to appear on this page &lt;a href=&quot;https://ci-builds.apache.org/job/Solr/job/Solr-Artifacts-main/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://ci-builds.apache.org/job/Solr/job/Solr-Artifacts-main/&lt;/a&gt; which will then include the fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18009701" author="houston" created="Thu, 24 Jul 2025 21:03:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=janhoy&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;janhoy&quot;&gt;janhoy&lt;/a&gt; this was in the 9.9 changelog on main. Since I&apos;m cleaning up the release notes as a part of the release, this should be changed to 9.10 or 10.0 (since it wasn&apos;t included in 9.9). Which do you want me to move it to?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18009709" author="jira-bot" created="Thu, 24 Jul 2025 22:44:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit fe84b633d4dd89795cfae8bb6277ebf15d19bc93 in solr&apos;s branch refs/heads/main from Houston Putman&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=fe84b633d4d&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://gitbox.apache.org/repos/asf?p=solr.git;h=fe84b633d4d&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

